  <section class="section white">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="label">Simple example</div>
      <h2>What this could look like in practice</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        This is what it can look like for a family in your community.
      </p>

      <div class="list-card">
        <h3>A practical example</h3>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>A family who normally would not make it to a site signs up using a phone or computer</li>
          <li>That household is included in a delivery plan for its area</li>
          <li>Meals are brought closer to where they live through a coordinated summer model</li>
          <li>Service is recorded in a way that supports program requirements</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section light">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="label">What this could unlock</div>
      <h2>The impact of extending reach</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        The value is not just operational. It is what becomes possible for families and for your community when summer meal access improves.
      </p>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">👨‍👩‍👧</div>
          <h3>More families reached at home</h3>
          <p>
            Families who are currently outside site access can receive meals more consistently throughout the summer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">📈</div>
          <h3>More consistent access for children</h3>
          <p>
            Reliable access helps children stay connected to the support your program provides throughout the summer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">🌍</div>
          <h3>Stronger connection to families across your community</h3>
          <p>
            More families across your community can be served consistently throughout the summer.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section white">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="label">How this works</div>
      <h2>You lead. We make it work.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Roosevelt School District 66 stays in control of the program. RuralBites supports the coordination so your team can focus on serving families without carrying every operational detail alone.
      </p>
      <p class="lead" style="margin-top:14px;">
        This is about making sure families who depend on your program during the school year can still be reached in the summer.
      </p>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="list-card">
          <h3>RuralBites handles</h3>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Coordinating delivery and working with vendors across your service area</li>
            <li>Supporting family enrollment so participation stays strong all season</li>
            <li>Keeping records organized as the program runs</li>
            <li>Working alongside your program from planning through final claim</li>
